This paper is about developing a framework for training conversational agents using weak supervision. The paper discusses using a search engine to find examples and data programming to automatically expand labels. This work is related to natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning, which are covered in the computer science sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses using data programming, which is a technique for generating training data, and this is related to machine learning and data mining, which are covered in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
